    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:checkhealth vim.treesitter` lists tree-sitter parsers that are on the runtimepath.\nIt would be nice to be able to see which query files are available for each language, too.\n\nnvim-treesitter's health check does this, but it only lists a table of queries that have been installed by nvim-treesitter.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:checkhealth vim.treesitter` should have a section, \"Treesitter queries\" that lists tree-sitter query files for each parser on the runtimepath and reports any errors that are thrown when trying to load the query files.",
