            "body": "> nvim-treesitter's health check does this, but it only lists a table of queries that have been installed by nvim-treesitter.\n\nYes, because that's the only thing that's easily accessible. Due to the query amalgamation feature, there's not a single point where the full list of (offending) queries is accessible. (See related issues on \"invalid node\" errors.)\n\nRight now, we can't do better than `:echo nvim_get_runtime_file('queries/<lang>/*.scm', v:true)`",
